[Tick-borne diseases like borreliosis and babesiosis seems to be slowly
spreading into new areas. The reservoir for _Babesia microti_ is mice and
deer. The period of peak transmission is during June. It appears that a
blood film for microscopy must now be standard in every patient with
unexplained fever who has visited Westchester County and adjacent areas.
